Package: srm
Title: Social Relations Model Toolkit for Network Analysis
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Cassy", "Dorff", email = "cassy.dorff@vanderbilt.edu", role = c("aut")),
    person("Shahryar", "Minhas", email = "minhassh@msu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Tosin", "Salau", email = "salaubol@msu.edu", role = c("aut")))
Description: Provides tools for estimating Social Relations Models (SRM) for
    network data. Decomposes network effects into actor, partner, and unique
    dyadic components, computes variance partitions and covariance structures,
    and supports permutation-based inference. Handles both cross-sectional and
    longitudinal networks, including bipartite (two-mode) designs. Integrates
    with the 'netify' package ecosystem for network construction, analysis,
    and visualization.
